%N A398011 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} sigma_2(k) * log(k) / k^4, where sigma_2(k) is the sum of squares of divisors of k (A001157).
%H A398011 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 379, Corollary 2.6.
%F A398011 Equals (Pi^6/45) * (log(A) - (log(2*Pi) + gamma)/6 - 10*log(A_3)), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%e A398011 1.128084747233529596887784007010506698798231202085596...
%t A398011 RealDigits[(Pi^6/45) * (Log[Glaisher] - (Log[2*Pi] + EulerGamma)/6 + 11/72 + 10*Zeta'[-3]), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398011 (PARI) (Pi^6/45) * (17/72 - zeta'(-1) - log(2*Pi)/6 - Euler/6 + 10*zeta'(-3))
